OL,3,CStarmer insists digital ID will never
OL,4,Cbe used to put Brits under surveillance
OL,6,FAlmost three million people have
OL,7,Fsigned a petition against it, which
OL,8,Fstates, "we think this would be a step
OL,9,Ftowards mass surveillance and digital
OL,10,Fcontrol, and that no one should be
OL,11,Fforced to register with a state-
OL,12,Fcontrolled ID system".
OL,14,FThe PM told ITV News digital ID cards
OL,15,F- which will be stored on smartphones
OL,16,F- will not be mandatory and no one
OL,17,Fwould be arrested simply for not
OL,18,Fhaving one, but said they will be
OL,19,Frequired for anyone wanting to work in
OL,20,Fthe UK.
